PRD: Business Hours & Batch Posting System

1. Overview

Cooperative operations have defined business hours — teller windows close at a set time, transactions are not processed after hours, and certain back-office operations must wait until the next business day. The system previously ran 24/7 with no concept of business hours. This PRD adds configurable business hours, holiday management, cutoff-based deferred posting, and a recurring batch job to post pending entries.

2. Goals

Allow cooperative administrators to configure business hours (open, close, cutoff) per cooperative

Prevent cash session creation and teller operations outside business hours

Provide configurable holiday management (one-off and recurring) that blocks business operations on those dates

Defer entry posting when created after cutoff time; batch-post them the next business day

Run a recurring Solid Queue job every 5 minutes to post deferred entries

3. Non-Goals

Support per-branch business hours (hours are cooperative-wide)

Support real-time clock-driven opening/closing (sessions are still manually opened by tellers)

Support multi-timezone scheduling (all remains UTC)

Modify existing entry reversal or idempotency semantics

4. Implementation

4.1 Data Model

Migration: `db/migrate/20260707130000_create_management_holidays.rb`

Table: `management_holidays`
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | bigint | PK |
| cooperative_id | bigint | FK, NOT NULL |
| date | date | NOT NULL |
| name | string | NOT NULL |
| recurring | boolean | Default false |
| timestamps | | created_at, updated_at |
| Index | | UNIQUE (cooperative_id, date) |

Config keys (stored in `Management::Configuration`):
- `business_hours_open` — integer hour (UTC), default 8
- `business_hours_close` — integer hour (UTC), default 17
- `business_hours_cutoff` — integer hour (UTC), default matches close

4.2 Models

`Management::Holiday` (`app/models/management/holiday.rb`)
- Scopes: `on_date(date)`, `recurring`, `between(start_date, end_date)`
- Class method: `self.holiday?(date, cooperative:)` — checks one-off + recurring holidays
- Recurring holidays match by EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date) and EXTRACT(DAY FROM date)

4.3 Services

`Management::BusinessDayService` (`app/services/management/business_day_service.rb`)
- `business_day?(date)` — true unless Saturday/Sunday or holiday
- `within_business_hours?(at_time:)` — current time between open and close hours
- `after_cutoff?(at_time:)` — current time at or after cutoff hour
- `next_business_day(from:)` — forward-skips non-business days
- Reads config keys at call time (not cached)

`Accounting::BusinessHoursPostingService` (`app/services/accounting/business_hours_posting_service.rb`)
- Wraps `PostEntryService`
- Decides immediate vs deferred posting based on:
  1. Explicit `post_immediately:` flag (default false)
  2. Business hours check via `BusinessDayService`
- If within business hours OR `post_immediately: true` → calls `PostEntryService.run!`
- If after hours → creates entry with `status: :pending` (no running balance update)

`Accounting::PostEntryService` (`app/services/accounting/post_entry_service.rb`)
- Added `post_immediately` boolean input (default true)
- When false: saves entry with status `pending`, skips running balance computation
- When true: existing behavior unchanged (status `posted`, running balances computed)

`Accounting::PostPendingEntryService` (`app/services/accounting/post_pending_entry_service.rb`)
- Transitions a single pending entry to posted
- Updates running balances using `AppendOnlyOverride`

4.4 Job

`Accounting::PostPendingEntriesJob` (`app/jobs/accounting/post_pending_entries_job.rb`)
- Scheduled every 5 minutes via `config/recurring.yml`
- Iterates `Entry.pending.where("posted_at <= ?", Time.current)`
- Posts each via `PostPendingEntryService`

4.5 Business Logic Integration

`Treasury::CashSession.for_today` — returns nil unless `within_business_hours?` (hard-block at model level)
`Banking::CashSessionService` — `open` returns error unless within business hours
`Treasury::SavingsTransactionService` — uses `BusinessHoursPostingService.post` instead of `PostEntryService.run!`
`Equity::BuySharesService` — uses `BusinessHoursPostingService.post`

4.6 Controller & Views

`Management::HolidaysController` — full CRUD
Routes: `resources :holidays` under `management` namespace
Views: index, show, new, edit, _form partial
All views follow existing management module conventions (layout "dashboard", `content_for :page_title`)

4.7 Seed Data

`db/seeds/demo_data.rb`:
- 3 config keys with defaults
- 8 recurring PH holidays (New Year, Araw ng Kagitingan, Labor Day, Independence Day, Ninoy Aquino Day, Bonifacio Day, Christmas Day, Rizal Day)

`bin/e2e-setup`:
- 3 holidays (Christmas Day, New Year's Day, E2E Test Holiday)

4.8 Scheduled Task

`config/recurring.yml`:
```yaml
post_pending_entries:
  class: Accounting::PostPendingEntriesJob
  schedule: every 5 minutes
  description: "Post deferred accounting entries"
```

