6. Design Decisions

Time zone: All calculations in UTC. Business hours config stores integer hours, compared against `Time.current.hour` (UTC).

Append-only compatibility: The existing DB trigger on `accounting_entries` already allows `pending → posted` transition. No additional migration needed.

No `source_after_hours` enum: The entry's `status` field (pending/posted/reversed) suffices to distinguish after-hours entries. Adding a source enum value would duplicate state.

Cutoff defaults to close hour: If no explicit cutoff is configured, `Management::BusinessDayService` falls back to `business_hours_close`. Most coops use the same value.

Business hours config is read at call time: Each check queries `Management::Configuration`. Not cached because values may change and the read is cheap.

7. Open Questions / Future Work

Per-coop timezone: Currently UTC only. If a coop operates in PH Time (UTC+8), the business hours config values need manual offset adjustment.

Per-branch business hours: Some coops may want branch-level hours. This would require scoping config and BusinessDayService to branches.

Holiday bulk import: Adding a CSV upload for holidays would improve UX for annual holiday declaration.

Cutoff grace period: Some coops want a 5-15 minute grace window after cutoff for in-progress transactions.

Late-night maintenance window: A configurable maintenance window that blocks ALL operations (not just outside business hours).

